               <head>Collection of Judeo-Persian poetical works.</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85070893">
                  <summary>A collection of Judeo-Persian poetical works.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="jpr-Hebr" />
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="1r" to="79r" />
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/49160204">אלישע בן
                  שמואל</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/49160204">Elisha` ben Shemuʾel,
                  active 17th century</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="jpr-Hebr-Latn-x-lc">Shāhzādeh u Ṣūfī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="jpr-Hebr">שהזאדה וצופי</title>
                     <incipit />
                     <note>
                        <p>The story of Barlaam and Josaphat in a Judaeo-Persian metrical version, based on
                    <title xml:lang="heb-Latn-x-lc">Ben ha-melekh veha-nazir</title> of <persName xml:lang="heb-Latn" type="standard" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/79061776" key="n88074427">Abraham ben Samuel ibn Hasdai</persName>
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <filiation>
                        <p>See also British Library Or. 4731, item 8; Or. 4744, item 1; Or. 10196, item
                  1.</p>
                     </filiation>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Meredith-Owens 1968, page 38.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="79r" to="83r" />
                     <author />
                     <title xml:lang="jpr-Hebr-Latn-x-lc">Ḥikāyat-i ān sih Yahūdān-i tājir</title>
                     <incipit />
                     <note>
                        <p>The story of Solomon and the three merchants, in verse.</p>
                     </note>
                     <colophon>"תמת אל כתאב ... שה זאדה צופי ... יום שני כ"ג לחדש מת"ת [=מתן תורה] שנת
                ושאבתם מיים ב’ש’ש’ו’ן’ לב"ע [=תרנ"ח המעתיק טעה ושכח להוסיף את ה האלפים של בריאת
                העולם] כתבתי בשביל הגביר ... כמוה"ר מ יהודא המתקרי באבאי בן ... כה"ר מ’ שמואל כ"ץ
                יקרא הוא זרעו וזרע זרעו ... הכותב הצעיר אנא עבדא זעירא רפאל מלמד הכהן ס"ט בכה"ר
                נתנאל יצחק אברהם מנדגאר אליעזר כ"ץ נ"ע" <locus from="82v" to="83r" />
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>Paper codex of the 19th century.</p>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>Paper with laid lines and chain lines; <watermark>watermark: Crest-like
                    device, surrounded with a belt-like motif and the motto 'PRO BONO PUBLICO', and
                    with the inscription below it: 'UNIVERSAL FOOLSCAP'.</watermark>
                        </support>
                        <extent>83 folios (iii+83+iii)<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>240</height>
                              <width>158</width>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height>163</height>
                              <width>100</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation>
                           <p>Foliation in Arabic numerals in pencil.</p>
                        </foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>Catchword on every page.</p>
                        </collation>
                        <condition>
                           <p>A few sages stain, smudged ink.</p>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="2">
                           <p>Left margin is even.</p>
                           <p>Ruling is visible.</p>
                           <p>Leaves were folded into two vertically, and then unfolded, that folding line
                    provides the division between the columns.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
